 wish it were.  </></>Jamie, do you have a favorite Bloody Mary recipe?  Inquiring minds want to know &#8211; and want to see it.  Please.</></>Dawna, this French place of yours has the right idea.  I too am a (fairly) early riser, so I prefer to treat brunch as lunch instead.  That way, I get to wake up my stomach with something that&#8217;s a little easier going down, and then I am happy to greet an eggs Benedict later.  I&#8217;m less apt to be starving, too, so I can fend off those inferior hash browns.</></>Dianka, the artichokes really &#8220;make&#8221; the dish &#8211; and especially with a few golden spots from browning in the butter.  Mmm.</p>
